All 455 tests pass. Three bugs were fixed in `inflection/__init__.py`:

1. **Line 29 — `pluralize` regex** (`category-categories`, `query-queries`, etc.): The replacement `r'\1ys'` was wrong — words ending in a consonant+`y` should become `-ies`, not `-ys`. Fixed to `r'\1ies'`.

2. **Line 169 — `camelize` function** (`Product-product`, `SpecialGuest-special_guest`, etc.): The lambda was calling `.lower()` instead of `.upper()`, so `camelize("special_guest")` produced `"special_guest"` instead of `"SpecialGuest"`. Fixed to `.upper()`.

3. **Line 229 — `ordinal` function** (11th, 12th, 13th, 111th, etc.): The special-case check used `number % 10 in (11, 12, 13)`, which can never be true since `n % 10` is always 0–9. Fixed to `number % 100` so that 11, 12, 13, 111, 112, 113, etc. all correctly return `"th"`.
